snippet.title: Veg vs Non-Veg On Air India!! ✈️🇮🇳
snippet.description:
NOTE: I filmed this before the recent tragic Air India incident. As a frequent flier, the news really shook me — it still scares me, to be honest.

I’m sharing this video to show the beautiful side of flying. My thoughts are with everyone affected. Praying for their strength — and for safer skies for all of us.

Flying from Mumbai to Bengaluru, I ended up reviewing dinner in economy class — both veg and non-veg meals — while also experiencing a little airline chaos before takeoff. From a surprise standby situation to clocking in my 10,000 steps at the airport, it was a journey even before boarding began!

Once in the air, the food service began and I was served two different meals. One had a spicy, comforting chicken curry; the other surprised me with a legit good dal makhani. And yes, I may have demolished the dessert entirely.

If you’ve ever wondered what Air India serves on short-haul flights, or whether veg or non-veg wins — this one’s for you.

#DCTEats #AirIndia #InflightMeals #EconomyClass #FlightFoodReview #FoodVlog #MumbaiToBangalore #ChickenCurry #DalMakhani #AirportLife #InflightExperience #BangaloreFoodie #FlightVlog #HonestReview #TravelEats

snippet.title: Starting a new chapter in Dubai with @KaranKundrraOfficial | @tejasswiprakash413
snippet.description:
Join me, Tejasswi Prakash, and Karan Kundrra as we start an exciting new chapter in our lives—right here in the heart of Dubai! 🏙️💖 From stunning city views to personal moments, this vlog captures the magic of change, growth, and togetherness.

**Follow me on:**

For business enquiry: tejasswi.team@gmail.com
Contact No: +91 8427586416 
Instagram id: https://www.instagram.com/richaandsauravworld
#ACTRESS #VLOG

Cinematographer and Video editor:- Ashish Mandal
Instagram ID:-   / https://www.instagram.com/ashmaneditors/


The video showcases Tejasswi Prakash and Karan Kundrra embarking on an exciting journey in Dubai, emphasizing the unique experiences they are having together.
Tejasswi expresses her initial excitement about exploring the city while Karan is away on a shoot, highlighting her desire to share her experiences with viewers.
She notes the challenges of being alone in a new city, reflecting on how she manages her day-to-day activities.

Culinary Adventures

Tejasswi shares her food experiences, trying out local dishes like Harira soup, described as a unique Arabic soup served with dates and lemon.
She emphasizes her aim to eat healthily while also indulging in local snacks, showcasing a balance between wellness and enjoyment.
The video features her tasting various dishes, highlighting her appreciation for authentic flavors and the culinary diversity in Dubai.
Daily Routine and Challenges

Tejasswi discusses her daily routine, including her skincare regimen and managing her work schedule independently while in Dubai.
She encounters minor challenges, such as forgetting cash for food orders and navigating local payment systems, which adds a relatable aspect to her experience.
Despite these challenges, she maintains a positive outlook, showcasing her resilience and adaptability in a foreign environment.
Cultural Insights

The video provides insights into the local food culture, with Tejasswi noting how international restaurants adapt traditional Indian flavors for a global audience.
She reflects on her cravings for home-cooked Indian dishes, which connects her personal experience with broader cultural themes of food and nostalgia.
The restaurant visits highlight a blend of traditional and modern culinary practices, emphasizing the richness of Dubai's food scene.

📸 Behind-the-scenes moments, candid conversations, and a glimpse into what’s coming next!

Don’t forget to LIKE, COMMENT & SUBSCRIBE to @tejasswiprakash413 for more personal, travel, and lifestyle content. Tap the 🔔 to stay updated!

Let us know in the comments — what's your dream city to begin a new chapter?

The video showcases Tejasswi Prakash and Karan Kundrra embarking on an exciting journey in Dubai, emphasizing the unique experiences they are having together.
Tejasswi expresses her initial excitement about exploring the city while Karan is away on a shoot, highlighting her desire to share her experiences with viewers.
She notes the challenges of being alone in a new city, reflecting on how she manages her day-to-day activities.

Culinary Adventures

Tejasswi shares her food experiences, trying out local dishes like Harira soup, described as a unique Arabic soup served with dates and lemon.
She emphasizes her aim to eat healthily while also indulging in local snacks, showcasing a balance between wellness and enjoyment.
The video features her tasting various dishes, highlighting her appreciation for authentic flavors and the culinary diversity in Dubai.
Daily Routine and Challenges

Tejasswi discusses her daily routine, including her skincare regimen and managing her work schedule independently while in Dubai.
She encounters minor challenges, such as forgetting cash for food orders and navigating local payment systems, which adds a relatable aspect to her experience.
Despite these challenges, she maintains a positive outlook, showcasing her resilience and adaptability in a foreign environment.
Cultural Insights

The video provides insights into the local food culture, with Tejasswi noting how international restaurants adapt traditional Indian flavors for a global audience.
She reflects on her cravings for home-cooked Indian dishes, which connects her personal experience with broader cultural themes of food and nostalgia.
The restaurant visits highlight a blend of traditional and modern culinary practices, emphasizing the richness of Dubai's food scene.

snippet.title: Never Do This Before Skydiving ⚠️☠️🚨 What Happened to me in Melbourne 🇦🇺 Australia Skydive? 😵
snippet.description:
Never Do This Before Skydiving ⚠️☠️🚨 What Happened to me in Melbourne 🇦🇺 Australia Skydive? 😵

In this vlog, we experience the thrill of skydiving in Melbourne, Australia 🇦🇺 — but things didn’t go as planned.
I made the mistake of not having breakfast before the jump, and that turned into a serious problem right after landing. 🤢

I started vomiting, felt dizzy, and for the next 4–5 days, I struggled with body pain and fatigue.
It was a painful reminder that skydiving without proper preparation is risky.

Yes, the view from above was breathtaking, and the experience was once-in-a-lifetime — but I’ll never do it again like this.
Next time? Only with full preparation and proper arrangements.

Watch till the end and learn from my mistake — this might just help you avoid the same situation.
